DS hwCMhq pf-14_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-15_">What Does is 22-Momme?</h1><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-17_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Think of Momme as a measurement like thread count in cotton. It describes the weight and density of silk. A higher momme means more silk strands in the fabric, making it heavier. For example, if a fabric weighs 19 pounds, the momme is 19. Momme comes in at anywhere from 11 to 25, with 22 being the perfect balance.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6579" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lkgTHX jrzygT pf-19_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fmBCVi iwpzju"><div class="sc-kfPuZi ihOOoE pf-20_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-21_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-22_">And what about 6a?</h1><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-24_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The way to classify silk is to grade&nbsp;it on a scale from A to C, with A being the highest quality and C the lowest. The numbers refine this scale further—3A, 5A, or 6A, with 6A being the top-tier quality. When you see a silk product graded 6A, it means it's the highest quality in that specific type of silk.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d4a7" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lkgTHX jrzygT pf-26_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fmBCVi iwpzju"><div class="sc-kfPuZi ihOOoE pf-27_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-28_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-29_">Lastly, what is 100% Mulberry?</h1><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-31_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"> Mulberry Silk comes from silkworms that feed on mulberry leaves. The silk they produce is the best for textile purposes. The '100%' means the fabric is entirely Mulberry silk, which is crucial. Some companies mix Mulberry silk with cheaper alternatives, but pure Mulberry silk is known for its softness and durability.</p><p class="sc-gIDmLj eMdhGW pf-33_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"> So, if you're looking for silk pillowcases go for 6A, 22-momme—it's the best choice. And if you're thinking about a silk pillowcase, consider Snoozy. Our pillowcases are made from 6A, 22-Momme 100% Mulberry Silk, offering unmatched benefits for your hair, skin, sleep quality, and allergies—benefits that cheaper silk or other fabric pillowcases simply can't match.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4fb2" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lkgTHX jrzygT pf-35_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fmBCVi iwpzju"><div class="sc-kfPuZi ihOOoE pf-36_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-37_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brSvTw kXcmVH pf-38_"><i>AND WHY GO the silk way?<br></i>The benefits are real</h1></div></div></div><div class="sc-kfPuZi ihOOoE pf-40_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-41_"><div class="sc-fZzbTk jHmpJs pf-42_ pf-r pf-r-ew pf-c-ct pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--ew-xs:1;--ew-sm:3" data-pf-type="ContentList"><div class="pf-c"><div data-pf-type="ContentListItem" class="sc-kexyCK bzJCqz rid-2"><div class="sc-kfPuZi ihOOoE rid-3 pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq rid-7"><h1 tabindex="0"